---json
{
  "layout": "layouts/t-bofu.njk",
  "permalink": "/accounting/bookkeeping/catch-up-bookkeeping/",
  "slug": "catch-up-bookkeeping",
  "tierClass": "section--tier-bofu",
  "bodyClass": "page--bofu",
  "title": "Catch-Up Bookkeeping Services · TechBrot",
  "description": "Bring backlogged books current — TechBrot catch-up bookkeeping for U.S. small businesses months or years behind. Fixed-fee, priced per month of backlog, named Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor. Typically 2–10 weeks.",
  "breadcrumb": [
    { "name": "Home", "href": "/" },
    { "name": "Accounting", "href": "/accounting/" },
    { "name": "Bookkeeping", "href": "/accounting/bookkeeping/" },
    { "name": "Catch-up bookkeeping" }
  ],
  "hero": {
    "eyebrow": "Catch-up bookkeeping",
    "heading": "Months behind. Maybe years. We can fix that.",
    "subheading": "A project-based catch-up that brings backlogged books current &mdash; missed transactions entered, every prior period reconciled against actual statements, payroll and sales tax verified, statements through the current month. Fixed fee, priced per month of backlog, named Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor. Typically 2&ndash;10 weeks.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=catch-up", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "inBrief": {
    "text": "<strong>Catch-up bookkeeping</strong> is a project-based engagement that brings backlogged books current &mdash; entering missed transactions, completing prior-period reconciliations against actual statements, verifying payroll and sales tax, and producing reliable financial statements through the current month. Fixed fee, <strong>priced per month of backlog</strong>, typically 2&ndash;10 weeks.",
    "source": "Distinct from cleanup (fixes a messy state) and monthly (recurring). Not affiliated with Intuit Inc."
  },
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "Catch-up starts here",
    "heading": "Let&rsquo;s see how far behind you actually are.",
    "lede": "Book a free 30-minute diagnostic call. We&rsquo;ll review your file, quantify the backlog, and tell you what catch-up will cost &mdash; in writing &mdash; before any work begins. No pitch, no obligation.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=catch-up", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  }
}
---

<section class="section section--compact" id="catch-up-bookkeeping-proof">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="proof-strip">
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>4&times;</b> Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>Months behind</b> brought current</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>Fixed-fee</b> written scope, first</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><b>1 business day</b> response</span>
      <span class="proof-strip__item"><span class="proof-strip__rating">5.0</span> 2 verified Clutch reviews</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="catch-up-bookkeeping-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The engagement</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What catch-up actually is.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Catch-up bookkeeping is a project-based engagement that brings backlogged books current. It covers missed transaction entry, period-by-period bank reconciliation against actual statements, payroll and sales-tax verification, and producing reliable financial statements through the current month. Most engagements take 2&ndash;10 weeks and are priced as a fixed fee against a written scope.</p>
      <p>Catch-up is distinct from <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/cleanup-bookkeeping/?intent=cleanup">cleanup bookkeeping</a> (which fixes errors in a messy state) and from <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/monthly-bookkeeping/?intent=monthly">monthly bookkeeping</a> (which is recurring). Many engagements combine catch-up with cleanup &mdash; clean up the existing periods, catch up the missing months, then transition to monthly.</p>
    </div>
    <blockquote class="pull-quote">
      <p>{{ debt.body | safe }}</p>
    </blockquote>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="catch-up-bookkeeping-signals">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Is it time?</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">If any of these sound familiar, the answer is yes.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for s in signals %}
      <div class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.opener | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="catch-up-bookkeeping-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Catch-up, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="catch-up-bookkeeping-deliverables">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The scope</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What catch-up actually delivers.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for d in deliverables %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="num">{{ d.num }}</p>
        <h3>{{ d.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ d.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="catch-up-bookkeeping-process">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The process</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">From first call to current books.</h2>
    </header>
    <ol class="process-diagram">
      {%- for s in process %}
      <li class="process-step">
        <p class="process-step__number">{{ s.num }}</p>
        <h3 class="process-step__heading">{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="process-step__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
        <p class="process-step__body"><strong>{{ s.when | safe }}</strong></p>
      </li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="catch-up-bookkeeping-decide">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Catch-up or cleanup?</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Which one do you actually need?</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Behind but structured is a catch-up. Messy or wrong is a cleanup. Many files need both &mdash; the diagnostic tells you which, in writing, before any work begins.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="vs-scroll">
      <table class="vs-table">
        <caption class="sr-only">Catch-up bookkeeping versus cleanup bookkeeping, by dimension.</caption>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Dimension</th>
            <th scope="col" class="vs-table__us">Catch-up</th>
            <th scope="col">Cleanup</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {%- for row in decide %}
          <tr>
            <th scope="row">{{ row.dim | safe }}</th>
            <td class="vs-table__us"><strong>{{ row.us | safe }}</strong></td>
            <td class="vs-table__concede">{{ row.other | safe }}</td>
          </tr>
          {%- endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="catch-up-bookkeeping-pricing">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Pricing</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Fixed fee, written scope, priced per month of backlog.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Rates run per month of backlog by complexity; a 12-month standard catch-up at $400/mo is a $4,800 fixed fee. Typical total engagements land between <strong>$2,000 and $20,000+</strong>. See the <a href="/pricing/?intent=pricing">bookkeeping pricing page</a> for ongoing monthly pricing after catch-up.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for t in tiers %}
      <article class="review-card">
        {%- if t.note %}<p class="review-card__role">{{ t.note | safe }}</p>{%- endif %}
        <h3>{{ t.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact"><strong>{{ t.price | safe }}</strong>{{ t.per | safe }}</p>
        <p class="review-card__fact"><strong>For:</strong> {{ t.forWhom | safe }}</p>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          {%- for b in t.bullets %}<li>{{ b | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="/contact/?intent=catch-up">{{ t.cta | safe }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="catch-up-bookkeeping-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who performs the work</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A named, credentialed local operator.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Every TechBrot catch-up is delivered by a vetted local operator &mdash; an independent accounting practice running under TechBrot&rsquo;s brand, standards, and infrastructure. You&rsquo;ll know exactly who is working on your books and how to reach them. Platform-level quality review backs every engagement, and if continuity is ever a question, the platform handles the transition without losing file context.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operatorSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="catch-up-bookkeeping-next">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Around the catch-up</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Catch-up is often part of a larger engagement.</h2>
    </header>
    {%- for n in nextSteps %}
    <div class="stack-8">
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p class="prose">{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="catch-up-bookkeeping-intake">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Start now</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Scope your catch-up.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Tell us how far behind you are and a Certified ProAdvisor replies within one business day with a written fixed-fee scope. Prefer the full intake? The <a href="/contact/?intent=catch-up">complete contact form</a> captures every detail.</p>
    </header>
    {%- set intakePrefix = "cub" %}
    {%- set intakeFormId = "catch-up-bookkeeping-intake-form" %}
    {%- set intakeIntent = "catch-up" %}
    {%- set intakeSourceType = "bofu-conversion" %}
    {%- set intakeFunnelStage = "BOFU" %}
    {%- set intakeLegend = "What we should look at" %}
    {%- set intakeNote = "Catch-up bookkeeping is the common reason businesses reach this page &mdash; add anything else you want scoped in the same call." %}
    {%- set intakeConsent = "I agree to be contacted by TechBrot regarding this catch-up bookkeeping inquiry." %}
    {%- set intakeSubmit = "Send the Discovery Brief" %}
    {%- set intakeReassurance = "No spam, no list, no obligation. A Certified ProAdvisor replies within one business day." %}
    {% include "partials/intake-form.njk" %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="catch-up-bookkeeping-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Common questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What people ask before scoping a catch-up.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="catch-up-bookkeeping-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="catch-up-bookkeeping-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
